snippet.textDisplay:
Great song. Respect Coke Studio@Pak.
However, someone please help me understand what greatness or glory the Pakistani army has brought to its people. Every war that they have fought was for an illegitimate political cause in which they very clearly lost. I can't understand the basis of this overcharged patriotic lyrics for the army. Sure, the lives of soldiers are valuable and the lyrics to that extent are well placed, but glorifying their deeds as saviours of people is I think incorrect if you see it from a world view of polity.
